    {
      "activities": [],
      "description": "Nonmagical ammunition is destroyed immediately after hitting the [[lookup @name lowercase]]{monster} and dealing any damage. Any nonmagical weapon takes a cumulative \u22121 penalty to attack rolls immediately after dealing damage to the [[lookup @name lowercase]]{monster} and coming into contact with it. The weapon is destroyed if the penalty reaches \u22125. The penalty can be removed by casting the Mending spell on the weapon.\n\nThe [[lookup @name lowercase]]{monster} can eat through 2-inch-thick, nonmagical metal or wood in 1 round.\n\nFoundry Note\n\nThis feature provides an Attack Penalty active effect that will modify a targeted weapon. Since this penalty can be applied multiple times to multiple nonmagical weapons, this active effect needs to be dragged from this item's Effect tab onto the target Item's weapons.",
      "kind": "special",
      "legendary_cost": null,
